    "uses": "Atorvastatin is commonly used for the treatment of hyperlipidemia, a condition characterized by high levels of lipids in the bloodstream. It is also utilized to reduce the risk of cardiovascular events in individuals with multiple risk factors or a history of heart disease. Additionally, atorvastatin may be prescribed to help manage conditions like familial hypercholesterolemia, where individuals have genetically elevated cholesterol levels.\n\nIn some cases, atorvastatin is also used for primary prevention in patients without a history of heart disease but who are at high risk due to factors such as diabetes, hypertension, or obesity. The drug's ability to lower LDL cholesterol and triglycerides while increasing HDL cholesterol makes it a valuable tool for improving overall cardiovascular health.",

